{"word":"κατερέω","slug":"κατερέω","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>κατερέω</b></el> <el>(attic <el>κατ-ερῶ</el>) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b>serving as <a href='S:future tense'>fut.</a> of the aor2 <a href='S:κατεῖπον'><el>κατεῖπον</el></a>\n<el>(<a href='S:perfect tense'>perf.</a> <el>κατείρηκα</el>) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>to speak against, accuse</i>, <el>τινός</el> <b><a href='S:Xenophon'>Xen.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Plato'>Plat.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:accusative'>acc.</a> <i>to denounce</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b><i>to say</i> or <i>tell plainly, speak out</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>:— <a href='S:passive signification'><a href='S:Passive Voice'>Pass.</a></a>, <el>κατειρήσεται</el> <i>it shall be declared</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}